2. WORKING PROCEDURE (Step-by-Step Commands)
Step 1: Update System
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

Step 2: Install Dependencies
sudo apt install python3-opencv python3-numpy gstreamer1.0-tools -y


✅ These are lightweight and already optimized for Jetson Nano Orin.

Step 3: Verify Camera Stream

Before running, make sure your mobile camera stream is live and reachable:

gst-launch-1.0 rtspsrc location=rtsp://username:password@ip_address:554/your_stream ! decodebin ! autovideosink


If you see your stream — it’s working!

Step 4: Run the Histogram Script
python3 live_histogram.py

Step 5: Controls

Press q → Quit the application

The window titled “RTSP Feed” shows the live video

The window titled “Live Histogram (BGR)” shows color intensity distribution
